<<speech "thalara">>Only the first glimpse. More will come, if you let it.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I didn‚Äôt think a few degrees of cheekbone would feel different. But it does. Like my smile knows it‚Äôs meant for court instead of campfire.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>That is the beginning of understanding. Not just of body but of presence. You will find new ways to be seen. But more importantly‚Ä¶ you will learn how to see yourself.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Do you think she‚Äôll be proud of me? The Queen?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ml_right_hand_mm_6]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ml_right_hand_mm_6
<<nobr>>
<<speech "thalara">>I think you will be. In time. That matters more than even a crown.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>And my hand‚Ä¶ will it be weaker now? I trained so hard to master the sword.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>It will not be weaker. Just different. You may wield a quill or a fan, a glance or a law, with the same precision you once gave to blade. Femininity is not the absence of strength it is strength reshaped.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Strange. I thought the hardest part would be pain. But it‚Äôs this‚Ä¶ knowing I‚Äôll never hold the hilt quite the same way again.<</speech>><br>
[[Move Forth|right_hand_ml_right_hand_mm_7]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ml_right_hand_mm_7
<<nobr>>
<<speech "thalara">>And yet, someday soon, you‚Äôll hold the realm itself in your hand. That is a grip far mightier than steel.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>You speak as if you've seen it before. Have you done this to others?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>I have guided a few across the threshold. Not all princes, not all queens. But every soul who braved the crossing came away changed‚Ä¶ and closer to truth. Yours will be no different.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Then‚Ä¶ let‚Äôs see who I become.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ml_right_hand_mm_8]]

<</nobr>>

