:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_1
<<nobr>>
<<speech "thalara">>You come back again. To call strength home. Tell me‚Ä¶ is it courage that brings you here or fear?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Maybe both. Maybe neither. All I know is I need to feel it again. The firmness. The grip that doesn‚Äôt hesitate.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>And what will you do with that grip, Caelan? Crush? Command? Or merely remember what it was like not to doubt it?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I don‚Äôt know. I just miss knowing what my hand is for. Right now, it trembles when it should clench. Reaches when it should guard.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_2]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_2
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Then let us show it another memory. One not of blade or brush, but of presence. The potion is stronger today stirred with wolfsbane root and charred oak. You‚Äôll feel its intent like a drum beneath your skin.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>The color‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs darker now. Like amber in stormlight.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Yes. It remembers fire. And it will rekindle what was dimmed. But it will not erase what you‚Äôve learned. No potion ever truly forgets.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Gods it bites. It‚Äôs crawling into the joints‚Ä¶ curling the fingers inward. They want to close now.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_3]]
<</nobr>>


:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_3
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>The muscle awakens. Old reflexes stir. The hollow places you once opened now fill again, slowly, deliberately. The grip returns, not as instinct but as intent.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>It‚Äôs like someone is rewinding me. Pulling thread back into tight knots.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>That is not failure. It is merely re-centering. Even queens must retreat at times. You are not choosing weakness or strength you are choosing understanding.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>My fingers‚Ä¶ they feel dense again. Less float. More presence. Like they‚Äôve reclaimed weight.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_4]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_4
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>They have. And with weight comes responsibility. You‚Äôve felt softness. Now feel command again. But hold it with wisdom, not fear.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>There‚Äôs a pulse in my palm. Familiar. Firm. But quieter than before.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Because now it knows balance. You are not the same boy who first clenched a sword. You‚Äôve touched tenderness. That changes the strike even if you strike again.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>So this isn't undoing. It's‚Ä¶ remembering another version of me.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_5]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_5
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Precisely. Let the hand flex again, if it must. Let it lead when the moment demands. But never forget it was also made to hold. To open.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>It‚Äôs done. I can feel it in the grip. It‚Äôs not the brute strength I had before‚Ä¶ but it‚Äôs closer. Firmer. Grounded.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Then let it serve you. Not as master or servant. But as instrument. You are not losing your path, Caelan. You‚Äôre feeling its curves.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>...Then I‚Äôll walk it with both hands. One that remembers war‚Ä¶ and one that remembers warmth.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_6]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_mm_6
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>That is the path of true rule. When the throne calls, let it find you ready not only to wield‚Ä¶ but to receive.<</speech>><br>
