:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_1
<<nobr>>
<<speech "thalara">>You have crossed the halfway mark. Do you feel it? How the flesh no longer answers to memory alone, but to possibility?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>It‚Äôs strange. I look at it and‚Ä¶ it doesn‚Äôt feel like mine anymore. Or maybe it‚Äôs becoming mine in a way it never was.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>That is not contradiction it is awakening. The hand you once forged in war now begins to shape the future in elegance, not edge.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>But it still remembers‚Ä¶ I still remember‚Ä¶ what it was like to hold steel, to draw blood.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_2]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_2
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>And you always will. That memory doesn‚Äôt vanish it deepens. Refines. Would you have this hand unlearn its strength? Or let it rise again with a new form of power?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>The runes are glowing. Why do they feel like they‚Äôre humming through my bones?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Because they‚Äôre not drawing power from the potion alone. They‚Äôre drawing it from you. From the will you carry. Your fear, your hope, your resistance‚Ä¶ your surrender. All of it feeds the flame.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I can feel the shape changing. Gods‚Ä¶ my wrist it's thin. Not weak‚Ä¶ but delicate. I could never imagine calling it that before.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_3]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_3
<<nobr>>
<<speech "thalara">>Delicacy is not weakness, Caelan. It is precision. It is intent. Like silk thread that holds royal banners stronger than chain when woven with purpose.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>The skin‚Äôs smoother. The fingers feel‚Ä¶ lighter. Like they don‚Äôt want to clench anymore. Like they‚Äôre meant to gesture. Or to touch gently, not grip hard.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Yes. They are beginning to express, not just execute. They are learning the language of grace. Of allure. And of command through presence, not pressure.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>My nails what‚Äôs happening? They‚Äôre shimmering. I didn‚Äôt think nails could glow.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_4]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_4
<<nobr>>
<<speech "thalara">>A reflection of your essence. They will always carry the echo of your bloodline, your magic, your decisions. You are not losing yourself, Caelan. You are refining your truth.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I want to say it still feels like me‚Ä¶ but I‚Äôm not sure it does. It feels like her. Like someone else‚Äôs hand is growing where mine used to be.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Then speak to her. The woman whose hand this is becoming. She is not a stranger. She is a part of you long ignored. Greet her not with doubt, but with dignity.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>‚Ä¶Hello. I suppose‚Ä¶ you‚Äôve waited long enough.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_5]]
<</nobr>>

:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_5
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>And she heard you. Look your fingers now rest in poise without effort. The muscles are still yours, but they obey a different rhythm now. One not born of resistance‚Ä¶ but invitation.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>It feels strange. Like the air touches it differently. Softer. Even the pulse in my wrist feels quieter.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>That is the heartbeat of transformation. Faint now but it will grow louder, stronger. You are no longer just reshaped you are becoming.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>So this is the threshold. After today, I don‚Äôt get to call it ‚Äúmy hand‚Äù in the same way anymore, do I?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_6]]
<</nobr>>


:: right_hand_ms_right_hand_fs_6
<<nobr>>
<<speech "thalara">>No. You call it yourself. Not what you held. Not what you lost. But what you have chosen to extend into the world. This hand will be your introduction. Your grace. Your authority. Your legacy.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Then‚Ä¶ I‚Äôll let it become what it needs to. Just promise me it will still know how to hold the weight of who I was.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>It will. And it will carry it not as a burden but as a root. And roots, my dear Caelan, are what let the blossom rise.<</speech>><br>
[[I feel the potion working in my right hand|use_success_potion_create_right_hand]]
